SkyGuide
SkyGuide is a weather-based place recommendation app that integrates real-time weather data with destination recommendations to ensure users can plan their activities perfectly according to the weather conditions. Whether you're looking for a sunny spot for brunch or a dry day for hiking, SkyGuide offers intuitive, personalized guidance to help you make the most out of every day.

Features
Real-Time Weather Data: Access up-to-date weather information to plan your activities.
Personalized Recommendations: Get suggestions for places and activities based on current and forecasted weather conditions.
User Preferences: Customize the recommendations by setting your preferences for temperature, weather type, and activities.
Safety Tips: Receive advice on what to wear and what to carry based on the weather.
Interactive Interface: Easy-to-navigate user interface that ensures a pleasant user experience.
Getting Started
Prerequisites
Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:

Node.js (LTS version)
npm (comes with Node.js)
React Native CLI
Android Studio or Xcode (for iOS development)
Installation
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/SkyGuide.git
cd SkyGuide
Install the dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install
Start the Metro Bundler:

bash
Copy code
npx react-native start
Run the app on a device or emulator:

For Android:
bash
Copy code
npx react-native run-android
For iOS:
bash
Copy code
npx react-native run-ios
Usage
After launching the app, you can:

Enter your location to receive weather forecasts.
Customize your preferences to receive personalized recommendations.
Explore recommended places and activities based on the current weather.
